node.text:
Meet Joswin, professional cinematographer and founder of Bike LA. When the pandemic hit and his work slowed down, Joswin turned his passion for bike-riding into his muse. His camera of choice? The Google Pixel. By documenting his rides and popular Los Angeles landmarks, he built a thriving community that feels like family.

Watch Joswin’s True Pixel story and see how his Pixel helped him grow Bike LA.

node.title: Leader of the Pack - Joswin True Pixel Story

node.text: #InTheHeights star @anthonyramosofficial is taking center stage with @wordupbooks, a multilingual community bookshop and art space run by local residents, and helping us shine a spotlight on their important work. Learn more about their shared connection to this community and the #GrowWithGoogle tools Word Up has used to further their impact → google.com/grow. #InTheHeights

node.title: Anthony Ramos shines a spotlight on Word Up Community Bookshop

node.text: In celebration of #Juneteenth, Local Guide @theAprilHamm is visiting historic places in New Orleans — like Congo Square and the Free People of Color Museum — and adding information about them to the map to make history more accessible. Her contributions show that being a Local Guide on @googlemaps is more than leaving reviews — it’s a way to share and commemorate history.

node.title: Preserving Black History on Google Maps

node.text: Fred Armisen (@sordociego) and fellow drummer Jason Barnes (@cybrnetx) first met while playing a show in 2019. Since then, Jason and a team of researchers finished development of a revolutionary TensorFlow-powered prosthetic drumming arm. Watch Jason demonstrate the capabilities of his new prosthetic as the two drummers reconnect and play together. 🥁

node.title: Forward Rhythm | Two Drummers with Fred Armisen and Jason Barnes

node.text: Legen-dairy LGBTQ+-led ice creamery, @biggayicecream, first sweetened the dessert scene in 2009. Since then, co-founders Doug Quint and Bryan Petroff have turned their original ice cream truck into popular locations throughout New York City. Want the scoop on how you can lend a hand to small businesses in your community? Each Big Gay Ice Cream flavor gives you a taste of how you can show support. #growwithgoogle

node.text:
Today’s #GoogleDoodle celebrates the life of Swedish DJ, record producer and songwriter Tim Bergling — also known by his stage name, Avicii — on what would have been his 32nd birthday. Tap the link in bio to read our interview with Tim's father, Klas Bergling, who started the Tim Bergling Foundation to combat the stigma of mental health among young people.

🎨: @alawinans 
🎨: @sophiediao 
🎨: @oliviawhen

node.text: On #InternationalDogDay, meet Rasa Gentiviatë Źiemienë, the founder of @dogoapp. Discover how she built her version of “a little dog trainer in your pocket” to help “pawrents” better connect with their furry friends, with support from @googleforstartups. 🐾

Meet the Fitbit Charge 5. 🔥
 
Our most advanced health and wellness tracker comes with a brighter color touchscreen, longer battery life, an EDA sensor to measure your body’s stress response, 24/7 heart-rate tracking, built-in GPS and more. Tap the link in our bio to learn more about the Charge 5.
